菲利普是我老公,我们结婚十七年了

618
00:45:42,800 --> 00:45:46,387
and I would at least expect you
to respect my feelings.
希望你至少尊重一下我的感情

619
00:45:46,428 --> 00:45:49,181
You must be more adult about these things.
你一定要更加成熟看待这些事

620
00:45:49,223 --> 00:45:51,141
Yeah.
没错

621
00:45:51,225 --> 00:45:55,396
Come on, Shaun.
There comes a time when...
拜,肖恩,也该是时候了...

622
00:45:56,480 --> 00:45:58,899
you just...
你得...

623
00:45:58,983 --> 00:46:01,026
gotta be a man.
当个男子汉

624
00:46:08,325 --> 00:46:10,870
I'm telling you, it's a fuss over nothing.
我告诉你,根本是大惊小怪

625
00:46:10,911 --> 00:46:12,872
Hello, Edward.
你好,艾德华

626
00:46:12,913 --> 00:46:15,457
- Hi, Barbara.
- My, how you've grown.
-你好,芭芭拉
-哇,你长这么大了

627
00:46:15,499 --> 00:46:18,961
You better believe it.
What happened? Why is he coming?
你最好相信吧
怎么搞的? 他怎会跟来?

628
00:46:19,003 --> 00:46:22,673
- It wasn't as easy as all that.
- Are we following you?
-并不全都那么容易
-我们跟着你们走吗?

629
00:46:22,756 --> 00:46:26,343
No, it's probably best if we...
Where's the car?
不,可能最好是我们...
车子呢?

630
00:46:26,427 --> 00:46:29,430
Hmm...I pranged it.
撞烂了

631
00:46:29,513 --> 00:46:31,140
You were parked.
你才停个车呀

632
00:46:31,182 --> 00:46:33,017
Yeah.
对

633
00:46:33,100 --> 00:46:35,603
I guess we'll have to take the Jag.
我猜我们得坐积架车了

634
00:46:37,188 --> 00:46:39,482
- Philip?
- What?
-菲利普?
-什么事?

635
00:46:39,523 --> 00:46:41,609
Look out!
小心!

636
00:46:43,360 --> 00:46:45,196
Christ!
老天!

637
00:46:53,537 --> 00:46:56,332
- Give me the car keys!
- You're not driving that car.
-车钥匙给我!
-你别想开那辆车

638
00:46:56,373 --> 00:46:59,585
Give me the car keys!
Ed, get Mum in the car.
车钥匙给我!
艾德,叫妈上车

639
00:46:59,627 --> 00:47:01,879
I'm on it.
没问题

640
00:47:01,962 --> 00:47:04,882
Don't worry about me.
Worry about your mother.
别担心我,担心你妈吧

641
00:47:06,050 --> 00:47:09,261
- Maybe I should drive.
- I've adjusted the seat now.
-也许该由我来开
-我座位调整好了呀

642
00:47:09,303 --> 00:47:11,138
Just be careful!
只要小心点!

643
00:47:21,982 --> 00:47:24,735
Can you please turn that noise down?
拜把那噪音关掉好吗?

644
00:47:26,320 --> 00:47:29,698
Are you all right, dear?
Would you like another tissue?
你还好吧,亲爱的? 面纸还要吗?

645
00:47:29,740 --> 00:47:33,202
I'd be fine if it weren't for that bloody racket.
要不是那该死的噪音,我就没事

646
00:47:33,244 --> 00:47:35,454
- It is a bit loud.
- Sorry, Barbara.
-是有点吵
-抱歉,芭芭拉

647
00:47:38,165 --> 00:47:40,668
You do realise this is
a 20 mile an hour zone?
你们晓得这里限速20哩吗?

648
00:47:40,751 --> 00:47:42,294
Oh, yeah.
晓得

649
00:47:45,256 --> 00:47:47,842
- Here.
- Mum, this won't take a second, all right?
-到了
-妈,一下子就好,行吗?

650
00:47:51,262 --> 00:47:55,558
- Have you still got the child locks on?
- Safety first, Shaun.
-你还装了幼童安全锁?
-安全第一,肖恩

651
00:47:55,599 --> 00:47:57,685
You can't...
你不能...

652
00:47:59,103 --> 00:48:01,689
Hey, man, watch the leather.
嘿,小心皮椅

653
00:48:04,108 --> 00:48:07,069
Keep moving. If there's any problems...
继续开,如果有麻烦的话...

654
00:48:07,111 --> 00:48:09,446
I'll do the honks.
我会按喇叭的

655
00:48:33,554 --> 00:48:35,598
'Hello?'
喂?

656
00:48:37,475 --> 00:48:40,144
Hello?
喂?

657
00:49:01,248 --> 00:49:04,043
- Guys, can you let me in?
- What are you doing?
-大伙,能让我进去吗?
-你在干嘛呀?

658
00:49:04,084 --> 00:49:06,879
I've come to get you.
我来接你的

659
00:49:19,016 --> 00:49:23,020
- What are you doing?
- I've come to take you somewhere safe.
-肖恩,你做什么?
-我来带你去安全的地方

660
00:49:23,103 --> 00:49:25,272
- We were safe!
- You don't know that.
-我们在这儿安全的很!
-你并不清楚

661
00:49:25,356 --> 00:49:28,442
There was two of them out there.
How many are there now?
之前外面才两个,现在有几个了?

662
00:49:28,526 --> 00:49:29,735
- Lots.
- Lots!
-一大堆
-一大堆!

663
00:49:29,777 --> 00:49:32,738
It only takes one of them
to know you're in here.
相信我,只要他们其中一个
知道你们在这里面就完了

664
00:49:32,780 --> 00:49:36,534
I tried calling but I couldn't get through.
I had to come up with a plan.
我一直打电话都打不通
我只好拟定一个计划

665
00:49:36,617 --> 00:49:40,079
- Oh, you made a plan?
- We have to get out of here.
-哦,你定了一个计划?
-我们必须离开这里

666
00:49:40,120 --> 00:49:42,790
If we don't, they'll tear us to pieces.
如果不离开,他们会把我们分尸的

667
00:49:42,873 --> 00:49:45,709
And that will exacerbate things for all of us.
那会使我们事情恶化的

668
00:49:45,793 --> 00:49:48,629
- Shaun...
- This is not about you and me.
-肖恩...
-这与你我的事无关

669
00:49:48,712 --> 00:49:50,714
This is about survival.
是生死攸关的事

670
00:49:50,798 --> 00:49:54,760
We need to be somewhere more secure,
somewhere we can stay alive.
我们需要去更安全的地方
一个可以活下去的地方

671
00:49:54,802 --> 00:49:57,054
- We're with you, Shaun.
- What?
-我们跟你走,肖恩
-什么?

672
00:49:57,137 --> 00:49:59,849
- We're with you.
- I'm not going out there.
-我们跟你走
-我才不要出去

673
00:49:59,890 --> 00:50:04,687
Daffs! I don't want to be torn to pieces
and if you think about it, neither do you.
大卫! 我不想被分尸
你若考虑过,你也不愿那样的

674
00:50:04,728 --> 00:50:07,481
- I'm not going if Lizzie's not going.
- She's going.
-如果小丽不走,我也不走
-她会走的

675
00:50:07,565 --> 00:50:09,733
- I'm not staying by myself.
- You're going, aren't you?
-我不要一个人留下来
-你要走,是不是?

676
00:50:09,817 --> 00:50:11,861
- Lizzie?
- Liz?
-小丽?
-丽兹?

677
00:50:16,657 --> 00:50:19,952
- All right, Flash, what's your plan?
- Great. I've got a car
-好吧,简单说说你的计划为何?
-太好了,我有辆车

678
00:50:19,994 --> 00:50:23,706
but it's gonna be a bit cramped now.
Has anyone got transport?
不过现在呢有点挤,还有人有车吗?

679
00:50:23,747 --> 00:50:25,791
- Yes!
- Great. Where?
-有的!
-太好了,在哪?

680
00:50:25,833 --> 00:50:28,711
Oh, no. Well, I've passed my test.
哦,不是! 我考到驾照了

681
00:50:28,752 --> 00:50:30,004
David?
大卫?

682
00:50:30,087 --> 00:50:33,632
I don't see the point
of owning a car in London.
我觉得在伦敦买车来开没什么用

683
00:50:33,674 --> 00:50:36,427
Look, just get any blunt objects together.
听着,拿任何钝器都行

684
00:50:36,510 --> 00:50:39,305
If you get cornered,
bash them in the head.
如果被围住,朝头部用力敲下去

685
00:50:39,346 --> 00:50:42,099
Keep together, stay sharp and follow me.
聚在一起,保持警觉并跟着我走

686
00:50:42,183 --> 00:50:44,560
So, what's the plan, then?
那计划到底为何?

687
00:50:44,602 --> 00:50:46,979
We're going to the Winchester.
我们要去温彻斯特

688
00:50:51,025 --> 00:50:52,902
OK? Let's go.
好了吗? 我们走

689
00:51:09,043 --> 00:51:11,128
- Come on.
- Where's the car?
-快点
-车子呢?

690
00:51:15,716 --> 00:51:17,885
What's up, niggaz?
怎么了,混混?

691
00:51:22,556 --> 00:51:26,644
Apologies for the cramped conditions.
Di, stay on David's lap.
很抱歉里头满挤的
小黛,坐在大卫的膝盖上

692
00:51:26,727 --> 00:51:29,772
Philip, hang in there, OK?
Ed, get there fast.
菲利普,撑着点好吗?
艾德,开快点

693
00:51:29,814 --> 00:51:32,107
And, Mum, this is Liz. Liz, Mum.
妈,这是丽兹! 丽兹,这是妈

694
00:51:32,149 --> 00:51:34,068
Hello.
你好

695
00:51:41,075 --> 00:51:42,493
Ed, be careful.
艾德,小心点

696
00:51:42,576 --> 00:51:44,703
- Is your dad all right?
- He's not my dad.
-你爸没事吧?
-他不是我爸

697
00:51:44,745 --> 00:51:47,248
- He's bleeding.
- I know! Ed, be careful.
-他在流血呢
-我知道! 艾德,小心开车

698
00:51:47,331 --> 00:51:50,000
Thought you wanted to get there fast?
你不是说要开快点吗?

699
00:51:50,501 --> 00:51:53,629
I want to get there in one piece!
Why are we going this way?
我想整个人好好的到达那里!
干嘛走这条路?

700
00:51:53,671 --> 00:51:55,756
Chill out, it's a short cut.
别紧张,这是捷径

701
00:51:55,840 --> 00:51:58,884
- That road goes to the Winchester.
- Shaun...
-那条路通往温彻斯特
-肖恩...

702
00:51:58,926 --> 00:52:03,264
- Liz, please!
- I don't understand why the Winchester?
-丽兹,麻烦一下!
-我还是不懂干嘛非要去温彻斯特?

703
00:52:03,347 --> 00:52:06,475
- It's a pub, it's safe, it's secure.
- They know us.
-那是个酒吧,那里安全
-他们认识我们

704
00:52:06,517 --> 00:52:10,604
- What makes it so secure?
- It's got big heavy doors and deadbolts.
-酒吧为何会安全?
-因为有厚重的大门和门闩锁

705
00:52:10,688 --> 00:52:12,565
And there's a rifle above the bar.
而且酒吧上方有把莱福枪

706
00:52:12,606 --> 00:52:17,278
- I would think that's deactivated.
- It's not. John's connected. Big Al says so.
-我想那把枪不能击发了
-才没呢! 约翰有关连,大艾尔说的

707
00:52:17,361 --> 00:52:19,446
Big Al also says dogs can't look up.
大艾尔也说狗不会辨识颜色

708
00:52:19,530 --> 00:52:20,990
- They can't.
- Can't they?
-们不会
-会吗?

709
00:52:21,031 --> 00:52:23,159
- Of course they can!
- Are you sure?
-当然会!
-你确定?

710
00:52:23,200 --> 00:52:26,745
Yes! The pub is the right place to go.
Everything is gonna be fine.
是的! 这酒吧是最好的去处
一切会没事的,我保证

711
00:52:26,787 --> 00:52:29,248
- Shaun...
- I turned it off, all right?
-肖恩...
-已经关掉了,好吗?

712
00:52:29,290 --> 00:52:31,500
What?
什么?

713
00:52:31,542 --> 00:52:34,879
- Being a father, it's not easy.
- What?
-当个父亲并不容易
-什么?

714
00:52:35,462 --> 00:52:39,800
You were 12 when I met you,
you'd already grown up so much.
你碰到你时,你那时才12岁
就已经长的很大了

715
00:52:39,884 --> 00:52:45,890
I just wanted you to be strong
and not give up because you lost your dad.
我只是希望你能坚强起来
别自暴自弃,因为你刚失去了父亲

716
00:52:46,974 --> 00:52:52,521
- Philip, you don't have to explain.
- No, I do. I always loved you, Shaun.
-菲利普,你不必解释
-不,我要,我一直很爱你,肖恩

717
00:52:52,563 --> 00:52:57,359
And I always thought
you had it in you to do well.
我一直认为你很有潜能

718
00:52:57,401 --> 00:53:01,739
You just need...m-motivation.
你只是需要点...激励

719
00:53:01,822 --> 00:53:04,366
Somebody to look up to and...
一个可以做为榜样的人,以及...

720
00:53:07,411 --> 00:53:09,455
I thought it could be me.
我以为那个人会是我

721
00:53:10,998 --> 00:53:14,001
Would you just...take care of your mum?
好好照顾你妈...好吗?

722
00:53:17,671 --> 00:53:19,757
There's a good boy.
这样才乖

723
00:53:22,843 --> 00:53:25,346
- Ed, can you pull over?
- Two seconds.
-艾德,靠边停一下
-等一下

724
00:53:28,015 --> 00:53:30,684
- Ah! Ed, please pull over.
- What for?
-艾德,麻烦靠边停
-为什么?

725
00:53:30,768 --> 00:53:33,646
- Just pull over!
- All right.
-靠边停就是!
-好啦

726
00:53:39,276 --> 00:53:40,736
Whoa, momma!
哇,妈妈!

727
00:53:40,778 --> 00:53:44,240
- What the hell are you doing?
- Chill out. Everyone's all right.
-你究竟在搞啥鬼呀?
-冷静点,大家都很好啊

728
00:53:44,281 --> 00:53:46,450
Stop telling me to chill out!
少叫我冷静!

729
00:53:47,451 --> 00:53:51,038
- And everybody is not all right.
- What's wrong?
-大家才不好呢
-怎么了?

730
00:53:51,121 --> 00:53:53,707
Mum, it's Philip, he's gone.
妈,菲利普去了

731
00:53:53,791 --> 00:53:56,335
- Where's he gone?
- Mum, he's dead.
-他去哪了?
-妈,他死了

732
00:53:57,378 --> 00:53:59,672
No, he isn't.
不,他才没呢

733
00:53:59,713 --> 00:54:01,715
Get out!
下车!

734
00:54:03,133 --> 00:54:05,427
Jesus!
老天!

735
00:54:05,469 --> 00:54:08,764
- Get it open!
- Ed, get the child locks!
-快打开!
-艾德,打开幼童安全锁!

736
00:54:08,806 --> 00:54:10,891
Quick!
快!

737
00:54:13,310 --> 00:54:15,312
- The child lock!
- Ed!
-幼童安全锁!
-艾德!

738
00:54:35,166 --> 00:54:37,293
- Now what?
- We keep moving.
-现在怎么办?
-我们继续前进

739
00:54:37,334 --> 00:54:41,130
- How do we get Philip out the car?
- We haven't got time.
-怎样把菲利普弄出车外?
-没时间了

740
00:54:41,172 --> 00:54:43,924
- We can't leave your dad.
- He's not my dad!
-不能这样丢下你爸
-他不是我爸!

741
00:54:44,008 --> 00:54:46,010
Mum, he was, but he's not any more.
妈,他过去是,不过现在不是了

742
00:54:46,093 --> 00:54:50,514
- I really think we could...
- That's not your husband in there. OK?
-我真的觉得我们可以...
-里头那个不是你老公,懂吗?

743
00:54:50,598 --> 00:54:54,935
It looks like him but there is nothing
of the man you loved in that car.
虽然外表像他,可是已经完全不是
你所爱的那个男人了

744
00:54:57,271 --> 00:54:59,398
Let's go, shall we?
可以走了吗?

745
00:54:59,440 --> 00:55:01,775
You're not suggesting we walk?
你不会是建议我们用走的吧?

746
00:55:05,029 --> 00:55:07,615
- Everybody OK?
- Yeah, we're having a whale of a time.
-大家没事吧?
-嗯,我们时间多的很

747
00:55:08,032 --> 00:55:11,243
Maybe we should all hold hands,
make a crocodile?
也许我们全该手牵手,连成一线?

748
00:55:11,285 --> 00:55:13,329
Do you know where we're going?
你知道我们走去哪吗?

749
00:55:13,370 --> 00:55:15,873
- David, come on.
- Sorry.
-大卫,别这样
-对不起

750
00:55:15,956 --> 00:55:18,334
- Do you, though?
- Yeah, totally.
-你知道吗?
-嗯,清楚的很

751
00:55:18,375 --> 00:55:19,960
Are we close?
快到了吗?

752
00:55:25,716 --> 00:55:28,177
We're pretty close.
非常接近了

753
00:55:28,219 --> 00:55:31,138
- Is your mum gonna be OK?
- Yeah, I hope so.
-你妈不要紧吧?
-嗯,希望如此

754
00:55:31,222 --> 00:55:34,099
- Did you contact your folks?
- They're in Antigua.
-你连络过你的家人吗?
-他们在安地瓜

755
00:55:34,141 --> 00:55:37,144
- Do you think this is happening there?
- I hope not.
-你认为那里也有发生这种事吗?
-希望没有

756
00:55:37,228 --> 00:55:40,272
About last night.
I know loads of things were said but...
关于昨晚的事
我知道我说了一大堆,不过...

757
00:55:40,314 --> 00:55:43,108
- You said this wasn't about us.
- No, it's not.
-你说这与我们的事无关
-是,的确无关

758
00:55:43,150 --> 00:55:46,070
- You said it was about survival.
- It is, but...
-你说是生死攸关的事
-是没错,不过...

759
00:55:46,153 --> 00:55:51,534
You're not just trying to prove something?
I meant everything I said last night.
你不是想证明什么吧?
我指昨晚我说的话

760
00:55:53,828 --> 00:55:57,164
- Maybe this isn't the best time to talk.
- OK.
-也许现在不是谈话最佳时机
-好的

761
00:55:58,249 --> 00:55:59,875
Shaun.
肖恩

762
00:55:59,917 --> 00:56:01,377
Yvonne.
冯妮

763
00:56:01,418 --> 00:56:04,213
- How's it going?
- Er, surviving.
-你怎样?
-还活着

764
00:56:04,255 --> 00:56:06,841
Hey, Liz. Long time no see.
嘿,丽兹,好久不见

765
00:56:06,924 --> 00:56:08,592
Hey, Yvonne.
嘿,冯妮

766
00:56:08,676 --> 00:56:11,512
Erm...this is my boyfriend, Declan.
嗯...这是我男朋友狄克兰

767
00:56:11,595 --> 00:56:13,639
Erm...my friends Mark, Maggie,
嗯...我朋友马克和梅姬

768
00:56:13,681 --> 00:56:17,184
- my mum and my cousin Tom.
- All right.
-我妈和我堂弟汤姆
-好了

769
00:56:17,268 --> 00:56:19,770
This is Shaun and his girlfriend Liz.
这是肖恩和他的女朋友丽兹

770
00:56:19,854 --> 00:56:22,815
- They've split up, actually.
- Oh, really?
-其实他们已经分手了
-哦,真的吗?

771
00:56:22,857 --> 00:56:25,025
- Yeah.
- That's a shame.
-对
-真可惜

772
00:56:25,109 --> 00:56:28,112
We should scoot.
Have you got somewhere you're going?
我们该走了,你们有要去什么地方吗?

773
00:56:28,195 --> 00:56:31,699
- Yeah, we're going to the Winchester.
- The pub?
-有,我们要去温彻斯特
-酒吧?

774
00:56:33,617 --> 00:56:36,370
- Yeah.
- Right, well. Good luck!
-对
-好吧,祝你们好运了!

775
00:56:42,293 --> 00:56:44,044
Hi.
嗨

776
00:56:44,128 --> 00:56:45,588
Hello.
哈

777
00:56:45,629 --> 00:56:46,755
Hi.
嗨

778
00:56:46,797 --> 00:56:48,591
Hello.
哈

779
00:56:48,632 --> 00:56:50,301
All right.
好了

780
00:56:53,053 --> 00:56:55,598
See? The Winchester's just over there.
看见没? 温彻斯特就在那边

781
00:56:55,639 --> 00:56:57,975
- Over where?
- Over there.
-哪边?
-那边

782
00:56:58,058 --> 00:57:00,603
Just over there, over the 20 garden fences?
就在那边,穿过二十个花园围墙吧?

783
00:57:00,644 --> 00:57:02,480
What's the matter, David?
你有病呀,大卫?

784
00:57:02,980 --> 00:57:05,191
Never taken a short cut before?
以前没走过捷径吗?

785
00:57:22,082 --> 00:57:23,709
Shaun.
肖恩

786
00:57:23,751 --> 00:57:26,545
I'm sure Jill and Derek live round here.
我确定吉儿和德瑞克住这附近

787
00:57:40,601 --> 00:57:44,730
Now, the Winchester
is just over that fence, all right?
过了那围墙就是温彻斯特,好吗?

788
00:57:44,772 --> 00:57:48,067
Everyone stay where they are, I'll...
Are we all here?
大家留在原地,我要...
人都到齐了吗?

789
00:57:48,108 --> 00:57:51,779
- One, two, three, four, five. Yes.
- There's six of us.
-一、二、三、四、五,到齐了
-我们有六个人

790
00:57:51,862 --> 00:57:54,114
Mum!
妈!

791
00:57:56,867 --> 00:57:58,911
I'm coming!
我来了!

792
00:57:58,953 --> 00:58:01,664
Mum, are you OK? Are you OK?
妈,你没事吧? 没事吧?

793
00:58:01,705 --> 00:58:04,542
I don't think Jill and Derek do live here.
我想吉儿和德瑞克不住这里

794
00:58:08,379 --> 00:58:10,923
Shaun?
肖恩?

795
00:58:11,966 --> 00:58:14,176
Are you all right?
你没事吧?

796
00:58:31,569 --> 00:58:34,280
What are you doing?
你在做什么?

797
00:58:36,407 --> 00:58:38,450
Shaun!
肖恩!

798
00:58:41,412 --> 00:58:43,247
Yes!
好极了!

799
00:58:44,915 --> 00:58:47,126
No, that's rubbish.
不,一点用也没

800
00:58:54,592 --> 00:58:56,802
- Ooh!
- Yes!
哇塞!

801
00:58:58,596 --> 00:59:00,890
Feel free to step in any time.
欢迎随时进来

802
00:59:00,931 --> 00:59:04,059
- You did all right.
- I didn't want to cramp your style.
-你做的不错
-我才不想学你那样

803
00:59:04,101 --> 00:59:06,270
I'm so sorry about that.
刚才的事我很抱歉

804
00:59:08,105 --> 00:59:10,191
Right.
好

805
00:59:11,525 --> 00:59:16,280
OK, everyone stay where they are.
I'm gonna check if the coast is clear.
好,大家留在原地
我检查一下路面安全了没

806
00:59:25,122 --> 00:59:27,208
- Is it clear?
- No.
-安全了吗?
-没有

807
00:59:27,291 --> 00:59:29,418
- How many?
- Lots.
-有多少?
-多的要命

808
00:59:39,637 --> 00:59:42,640
Oh, well, that is just great.
哦,真是好极了

809
00:59:42,723 --> 00:59:44,892
There are a fair few of them, yes.
外头好多呢

810
00:59:44,975 --> 00:59:48,312
I trust Shaun has another genius scheme
up his sleeve?
我竟然相信肖恩还会有高明过人的对策?

811
00:59:48,395 --> 00:59:50,564
This is hardly constructive, David!
这话一点建设性也没,大卫!

812
00:59:50,648 --> 00:59:54,443
- We should have stayed at the flat.
- Why didn't you?
-我们早该留在公寓里
-那你为何没留在那里?

813
00:59:54,485 --> 00:59:58,864
Because... Because, because of...
Captain Wow.
因为...因为,因为...哇队长

814
00:59:58,906 --> 01:00:02,326
- Will you stop it?
- We'll get nowhere moaning.
-你住嘴行吗?
-放马后炮也于事无补

815
01:00:10,334 --> 01:00:12,920
Right, let's all shake out.
Get nice and limber.
好,我们抖抖双手,活动一下筋骨

816
01:00:12,920 --> 01:00:15,506
Or not.
或者免了

817
01:00:16,423 --> 01:00:20,135
Take another look at the way he moves.
Remember, very limp.
再看一遍他的动作
记住,要非常蹒跚

818
01:00:20,177 --> 01:00:25,683
Almost like sleepwalking. Look at the face,
it's vacant with a hint of sadness.
差不多像梦游一样,看看脸部
眼神空洞带点悲伤味道

819
01:00:25,766 --> 01:00:28,018
Like a drunk who's lost a bet.
就像赌输了的酒鬼

820
01:00:28,102 --> 01:00:30,146
OK, let's try, shall we? Liz.
好,来试试看吧? 丽兹

821
01:00:33,941 --> 01:00:38,154
Nice. Good vocal work.
OK. Barbara, that's excellent.
不错,声音做的不错
好的,芭芭拉,那表情太棒了

822
01:00:38,195 --> 01:00:40,698
Sorry, dear, I was miles away.
抱歉,亲爱的,我刚刚分神了

823
01:00:40,781 --> 01:00:43,492
- D-Daffs.
- Uh.
大卫

824
01:00:43,534 --> 01:00:45,536
- Come on!
- Urgh.
-快点!
-呃

825
01:00:45,619 --> 01:00:48,998
It's mournful, sorrowful,
you're dead and you hate it. Go.
带点呻吟、悲伤
你死了而且你讨厌那样,开始

826
01:00:49,039 --> 01:00:50,791
Uuurgh.
呃

827
01:00:50,875 --> 01:00:53,794
- Much better. Ed.
- I'll do it on the night.
-好多了,艾德换你
-我晚上才会做

828
01:00:53,878 --> 01:00:56,172
This is the night!
现在就是晚上!

829
01:00:56,213 --> 01:00:58,632
- What is that?
- What about yours?
-那是啥呀?
-那你呢?

830
01:00:58,716 --> 01:01:01,677
Who died and made you
fucking king of the zombies?
谁死了让你变成该死的僵尸王?

831
01:01:01,719 --> 01:01:03,387
Don't...
别...

832
01:01:06,140 --> 01:01:08,100
Yeah, that's pretty good.
嗯,那样很棒

833
01:01:08,142 --> 01:01:14,064
Right, let's all try together, shall we?
One, two, three.
好,大家一起来试试看,好吗?
一、二、三

834
01:02:08,369 --> 01:02:10,287
Go, go, go, go.
快,快,快,快

835
01:02:12,540 --> 01:02:15,042
Shit! Get round me, get round me!
该死! 围住我,围住我!

836
01:02:15,125 --> 01:02:19,547
John? John, Bernie, are you there?
It's Shaun and Ed. We come in all the time.
约翰? 约翰、柏妮,你们在吗?
是肖恩和艾德,我们常来的

837
01:02:20,464 --> 01:02:22,716
- They can hear you.
- We do the quiz.
-他们听见你了
-我们有问题了

838
01:02:22,800 --> 01:02:24,301
- They know.
- Stay in character!
-他们晓得了
-继续装死人样!

839
01:02:24,385 --> 01:02:27,596
- I can't see them.
- Shaun, we have to get inside.
-我看不见他们
-肖恩,我们必须进去

840
01:02:27,638 --> 01:02:30,266
- Break the window.
- We'll be exposed!
-破窗而入
-我们会曝光的!

841
01:02:30,307 --> 01:02:33,102
- Break the window!
- Is there another way in?
-打破窗子!
-还有别的路进去吗?

842
01:02:33,144 --> 01:02:35,187
Yeah, there's...
嗯,有个...

843
01:02:36,230 --> 01:02:38,691
Two seconds. Hey, Noodle.
等我一下! 嘿,面条

844
01:02:38,732 --> 01:02:41,485
- 'All right?'
- Yeah, man, I can't talk now.
-好了吗?
-老兄,我现在不方便讲话

845
01:02:41,569 --> 01:02:44,405
- 'You get anything yet?'
- I got nothing.
-拿到货了吗?
-没有

846
01:02:44,488 --> 01:02:47,408
I'm in the middle of something.
Yeah, it's weird.
我现在有事在忙,对,很奇怪

847
01:02:47,491 --> 01:02:51,328
- Oi! What are you doing?
- What are you doing? You stupid moron.
-噢! 你在干嘛呀?
-你在干嘛? 超级大白痴

848
01:02:51,412 --> 01:02:53,956
- Fuck off.
- You fuck off!
-滚开
-你才滚开!

849
01:02:53,998 --> 01:02:57,543
Fuck fucking off! I've spent an entire life...
该死的滚开! 我这辈子都在...

850
01:02:57,585 --> 01:03:00,838
Look at me. I've spent my entire life
sticking up for you
看着我! 我这辈子都在支持袒护你

851
01:03:00,921 --> 01:03:04,175
and all you ever do is fuck things up
and make me look stupid.
你却只会把事情搞砸,令我难堪

852
01:03:04,258 --> 01:03:07,344
I'm not gonna let you do it any more.
Not today!
我不会再让你这样了
今天不行!

853
01:03:07,428 --> 01:03:09,388
Shaun.
肖恩

854
01:03:09,430 --> 01:03:10,723
Oh.
哦

855
01:03:18,105 --> 01:03:20,941
You were saying about another way in?
你刚说还有别的路进去?

856
01:03:21,025 --> 01:03:23,110
Yeah, there's a...
对,有条...

857
01:03:23,194 --> 01:03:25,779
What are you doing?
你在干嘛呀?

858
01:03:26,947 --> 01:03:30,201
- No!
- Get inside.
-不!
-进去

859
01:03:30,284 --> 01:03:34,038
No, they'll follow us.
Keep up the act, I'll have to do something.
不行,他们会跟我们进去的
继续表演,我得想个办法

860
01:03:34,121 --> 01:03:38,083
- What do you mean do something?
- Hello, hello, over here!
-你说想办法是什么意思?
-喂,喂,这边!

861
01:03:38,125 --> 01:03:42,296
Come on, that's it.
Come on, that's it, over here!
快点,这就对了
快点,就是这样,靠过来!

862
01:03:42,379 --> 01:03:45,382
Over here! Come on. Oh, bollocks.
这边! 快点! 哦,混帐东西

863
01:03:45,466 --> 01:03:48,427
- Wait till I've gone then get inside.
- Gone where?
-等我走了再进去
-走去哪?

864
01:03:48,469 --> 01:03:54,308
I won't be long, I promise. Come on,
you pasty-faced fuckers, let's go! Follow me.
不会很久的,我保证
来吧,你们这些行尸走肉,我们走! 跟我来

865
01:03:54,391 --> 01:03:57,812
Come on, this way, that's it!
快点,这边,没错!

866
01:03:57,895 --> 01:04:01,774
Come on. This way, follow me.
Come on, follow me.
快点,这边,跟我来
快点,跟我来

867
01:04:01,816 --> 01:04:05,402
Come and get it. It's a running buffet.
来抓呀,流动餐车唷

868
01:04:05,486 --> 01:04:07,655
All you can eat!
通通随你们吃!

869
01:04:07,738 --> 01:04:09,782
Shall we go in, then?
可以进去了吗?

870
01:04:17,998 --> 01:04:21,502
- Come on, Barbara. Leave those.
- I think they're for me.
-快点,芭芭拉,别管那些花了
-我想花是要送我的

871
01:04:41,438 --> 01:04:44,150
- He's been gone a good 20 minutes.
- 17.
-他已经去了20分钟了
-17分钟

872
01:04:44,358 --> 01:04:49,822
Either way, we need to think about blocking
up this window. We're totally exposed.
没差啦,我们必须考虑堵住窗户
我们完全曝光

873
01:04:49,864 --> 01:04:53,450
- How will Shaun get back in?
- I'm sure he'll knock.
-肖恩要怎样进来?
-我相信他会敲门的

874
01:04:55,119 --> 01:04:58,080
- Let's get some lights on.
- David, wait!
-开点灯吧
-大卫,等一下!

875
01:04:59,456 --> 01:05:02,001
- Power's off.
- That's a good thing.
-没电
-那是好事

876
01:05:02,042 --> 01:05:05,504
- We mustn't advertise our whereabouts.
- No, of course not.
-我们不可曝露我们的所在
-对,当然不行

877
01:05:05,546 --> 01:05:09,550
- Do we, David?
- No, of course not, Lizzie.
-对吗,大卫?
-对,当然不行,小丽

878
01:05:09,633 --> 01:05:11,594
I'm just being proactive.
我只是做好预防准备

879
01:05:11,635 --> 01:05:16,056
There's no lights, no power.
And there's a hole in the window.
没灯光、没电力,窗户还有个破洞

880
01:05:16,140 --> 01:05:19,768
- You did that, you twat.
- Somebody had to do something!
-是你这家伙干的好事
-有些事总得有人去做!

881
01:05:19,810 --> 01:05:23,731
We were in a spot of bother. Somebody
has to take control of the situation
我们身在虎穴,得要有人来控制情况

882
01:05:23,814 --> 01:05:28,110
and if none of you are prepared
to accept that responsibility
如果你们没人准备扛下那重责大任

883
01:05:28,152 --> 01:05:31,322
then perhaps...I should.
那或许...该由我来扛

884
01:05:31,405 --> 01:05:34,783
- Will Shaun be gone long?
- He'll be back soon.
-肖恩会一去不回吗?
-他很快就会回来的

885
01:05:34,825 --> 01:05:37,745
- How do you know?
- I don't think he'd leave us.
-你怎知道?
-我认为他不会丢下我们不管

886
01:05:37,828 --> 01:05:44,043
Wouldn't he? How can you trust a man
you binned for being unreliable?
不会吗? 你怎能信任一个
你觉得不可靠的人呢?

887
01:05:44,084 --> 01:05:48,714
A man whose idea of a romantic nightspot
is also an impenetrable fortress.
一个把浪漫夜总会
当成固若金汤城堡的人

888
01:05:48,756 --> 01:05:51,884
This is a pub! We are in a pub!
What are we going to do?
这是间酒吧! 我们在酒吧里!
我们要做什么?

889
01:05:51,926 --> 01:05:54,553
I could get a round in.
我可以喝一杯

890
01:05:54,595 --> 01:05:58,390
Let's just wait for Shaun. We'll barricade
the window when he gets back.
我们等肖恩回来就是
他一回来,我们就把窗户堵死

891
01:05:58,432 --> 01:06:01,519
What then? How long?
Days? Weeks? A month?
什么时候? 等多久?
几天? 几星期? 一个月?

892
01:06:01,602 --> 01:06:03,771
- What are we going to eat?
- Toasties!
-我们要吃什么?
-土司!

893
01:06:03,854 --> 01:06:07,441
- There's a Breville out back.
- Great. Saved by nibbles.
-后面有间布列维尔
-太好了,靠零嘴救命

894
01:06:07,525 --> 01:06:09,819
Must be why Shaun took us here
before he left.
难怪肖恩离开前先带我们来这里

895
01:06:09,860 --> 01:06:13,989
- He's coming back!
- Why? Because he promised?
-他就快回来了!
-为什么? 因为他保证过吗?

896
01:06:14,031 --> 01:06:19,119
If he does, do you think his master plan
will be anything more than eating peanuts?
真要回来的话,你觉得他的超级计划
除了吃花生会能有什么吗?

897
01:06:19,203 --> 01:06:22,331
Is he just gonna stroll in
and suddenly everything's OK?
还是他只要走进来
突然间一切就没事了?

898
01:06:22,373 --> 01:06:26,961
I don't know, David!
I don't know any more than you do.
我不知道,大卫!
我不比你知道的还多

899
01:06:27,044 --> 01:06:31,590
But what I do know is that we're here now
and we have to make the best of it.
但我知道的是我们现在在此
而我们必须善加利用

900
01:06:33,300 --> 01:06:36,262
- Ed, get me a double vodka.
- Right you are.
-艾德,给我一杯双份伏特加
-没问题

901
01:06:36,303 --> 01:06:39,431
I'll have a drink too.
Would you like a drink, Barbara?
我也要喝一杯
你要吗,芭芭拉?

902
01:06:39,473 --> 01:06:41,684
- Hello.
- Right, great, fuck it.
-哈
-对,好极了,管它的

903
01:06:41,725 --> 01:06:45,396
We'll have a party
and get completely smashed.
我们来开个派对,喝个酩酊大醉

904
01:06:45,479 --> 01:06:49,191
We've got our nibbles.
We've got our Mini Cheddars.
我们有零嘴,有迷你乳酪

905
01:06:49,233 --> 01:06:52,820
- David!
- We got Twiglets. Oh, look, hog lumps.
-大卫!
-我们有鱿鱼丝! 哦,看,猪肉豆干

906
01:06:58,242 --> 01:06:59,785
Pickle!
小捣蛋!

907
01:06:59,827 --> 01:07:01,579
Hello, Mum. You all right?
你好,妈,你没事吧?

908
01:07:01,662 --> 01:07:03,706
- Everybody OK?
- Yeah.
-大家没事吧?
-是的

909
01:07:03,747 --> 01:07:06,000
- Any sign of John and Bernie?
- No.
-有看到约翰和柏妮的踪影吗?
-没有

910
01:07:06,083 --> 01:07:08,294
- Check upstairs?
- It's locked.
-楼上查过没?
-上锁了

911
01:07:08,335 --> 01:07:10,880
- Phones?
- Dead. Same as the power.
-电话呢?
-不通,电力也不通

912
01:07:10,921 --> 01:07:14,967
- OK...
- Nice of you to join us.
-好的...
-很高兴你能归队

913
01:07:15,009 --> 01:07:17,636
Yeah, well, I promised, didn't l?
对,我保证过,不是吗?

914
01:07:23,434 --> 01:07:26,270
How did you lose them?
你怎样摆脱他们的?

915
01:07:27,855 --> 01:07:31,525
I just gave them the slip.
Wasn't difficult. They're not all that.
我只是甩掉他们,不太困难
他们没那么聪明

916
01:07:31,609 --> 01:07:34,361
- Well, how did you get in?
- The back door.
-那你怎样进来的?
-从后门

917
01:07:34,445 --> 01:07:36,906
I tried to tell you
before you smashed the window.
你打破窗户前我就一直想告诉你

918
01:07:36,947 --> 01:07:40,326
But it wasn't me blowing our cover
by arguing with my boyfriend.
但是跟男朋友吵架
破坏我们伪装的人可不是我

919
01:07:40,367 --> 01:07:44,163
- He's not my boyfriend.
- Might be a bit warm, the cooler's off.
-他不是我男朋友
-可能有点温热,冰箱没电了

920
01:07:44,205 --> 01:07:46,332
Thanks, babe.
谢了

921
01:07:47,875 --> 01:07:49,835
So, what's the plan, then?
那计划呢?

922
01:07:51,879 --> 01:07:54,548
Would anyone like a peanut?
有谁想吃花生吗?

923
01:08:04,558 --> 01:08:06,727
Why don't you do your Clyde?
你何不扮演一下克莱德?

924
01:08:06,811 --> 01:08:09,814
Has anyone seen
Every Which Way But Loose?
有人看过电影《永不低头》吗?

925
01:08:09,897 --> 01:08:12,817
Ed does the most amazing
impression of the orang-utan.
艾德模仿红毛猩猩微妙微肖

926
01:08:12,900 --> 01:08:15,569
- No, it's not.
- It is. Come on. Do it.
-不,才不会呢
-会,快点表演吧

927
01:08:15,653 --> 01:08:18,447
- No, no.
- But it's brilliant. Come on.
-不,不
-不过很棒的,快啦

928
01:08:18,489 --> 01:08:21,659
- You've built it up too much.
- No, just do it.
-你说的太夸张了
-不会,只管表演就是

929
01:08:21,742 --> 01:08:24,620
Everyone wants to see it.
We could do with a laugh.
大家都很想看,我们可以开怀一笑

930
01:08:24,662 --> 01:08:27,248
Do it, do it, do it, do it. Come on, do it.
快,快,快,快,快表演吧

931
01:08:27,331 --> 01:08:29,416
I'm not a performing monkey.
我又不是杂耍猴子

932
01:08:31,919 --> 01:08:35,256
- The power's on.
- It's not, I tried it earlier.
-有电了
-不是,我之前试过了

933
01:08:35,339 --> 01:08:39,260
The streetlights are on.
I'll flip the fuses, we can watch television.
街灯亮了
打开保险丝开关就可以看电视了

934
01:08:39,343 --> 01:08:43,139
- What about the lights?
- Yes. Don't advertise our whereabouts.
-那电灯怎么办?
-没错,不可曝露我们的行踪

935
01:08:43,180 --> 01:08:47,017
The lights are on a separate circuit.
Just flip the mains breakers.
电灯是分开来的电路
只要打开主断电器就好

936
01:08:47,101 --> 01:08:49,436
It's quite simple, David.
相当简单,大卫

937
01:09:17,381 --> 01:09:20,050
- Is that it?
- That's it.
-有了吗?
-有了

938
01:09:46,243 --> 01:09:49,747
Liz, erm...have you got a quid?
丽兹...你有铜板吗?

939
01:09:54,668 --> 01:09:56,295
Erm...Yeah.
有的

940
01:10:00,841 --> 01:10:03,135
Never anything on, is there?
根本没节目

941
01:10:07,765 --> 01:10:09,517
What?
怎么?

942
01:10:11,519 --> 01:10:15,606
- I think we might have a bit of a problem.
- What do you mean?
-我想我们可能有点麻烦了
-什么意思?

943
01:10:19,610 --> 01:10:23,447
- They followed me.
- I thought you said you gave them the slip.
-他们跟随了我
-你不是说甩掉他们了吗?

944
01:10:23,531 --> 01:10:25,866
Yeah.
没错

945
01:10:25,950 --> 01:10:30,538
Well, we'll just have to be
extra quiet then, won't we?
那我们只好格外安静点

946
01:10:31,956 --> 01:10:34,041
What?
怎么?

947
01:10:35,876 --> 01:10:38,295
Ed, no!
艾德,不!

948
01:10:38,379 --> 01:10:40,464
Turn it off!
关掉!

949
01:11:11,996 --> 01:11:13,914
Shit!
该死!

950
01:11:13,998 --> 01:11:16,667
- Where the hell did he come from?
- I dunno.
-他到底从哪冒出来的?
-不知道

951
01:11:20,588 --> 01:11:23,632
- Who put this on?
- It's on random.
-谁放这首歌的?
-是随机播放的

952
01:11:23,674 --> 01:11:26,927
Dianne, get Mum somewhere safe.
David, kill the Queen.
黛安,带妈去安全场所
大卫,叫《皇后》别唱了

953
01:11:27,011 --> 01:11:28,762
- What?!
- The jukebox!
-什么?!
-自动点唱机!

954
01:11:28,846 --> 01:11:31,515
- Liz, Ed, grab a weapon.
- What about the rifle?
-丽兹、艾德,去拿武器
-莱福枪怎样?

955
01:11:31,599 --> 01:11:33,642
- Cocktails?
- What do you mean?
-鸡尾酒?
-什么意思?

956
01:11:33,684 --> 01:11:37,188
The flaming spirits
Get a rag in, light it.
燃烧的灵魂
塞点破布,然后点火

957
01:11:37,271 --> 01:11:40,316
- But the whole place could go up.
- What, then?
-但整间屋子可能会着火
-那怎么办?

958
01:11:40,357 --> 01:11:42,318
How about pool?
撞球杆如何?

959
01:11:42,359 --> 01:11:45,696
* Don't stop me now
"此刻别阻止我"

960
01:11:45,779 --> 01:11:47,740
* Don't stop me
"别阻止我"

961
01:11:47,781 --> 01:11:51,035
- * Cos I'm having... *
- John, it's time at the bar.
-"因为我正..."
- 约翰,该棒打老虎了

962
01:11:51,118 --> 01:11:54,914
* I'm a shooting star
leaping through the sky like a tiger
"我是划过天际的流星,宛如猛虎"

963
01:11:54,955 --> 01:11:58,584
* Defying the laws of gravity
"违抗着地心引力"

964
01:11:58,626 --> 01:12:02,922
* I'm a racing car passing by
like Lady Godiva
"我是疾速奔驰的赛车,恰似戈瓦迪夫人"

965
01:12:02,963 --> 01:12:05,424
* I'm gonna go, go, go
"我要冲冲冲"

966
01:12:05,466 --> 01:12:08,010
* There's no stopping me
"无可阻挡我"

967
01:12:08,052 --> 01:12:10,346
* I'm burning through the sky...
"我要燃烧整片天空..."

968
01:12:10,429 --> 01:12:13,307
- I can't find the switches!
- Then get the fuses!
-我找不到开关!
-那就拔掉保险丝!

969
01:12:13,724 --> 01:12:15,684
* That's why they call me Mister Fahrenheit
"所以人们叫我华氏先生"

970
01:12:15,726 --> 01:12:17,937
* I'm travelling at the speed of light
"我以光速穿梭旅行"

971
01:12:17,978 --> 01:12:21,899
* I wanna make
a supersonic man out of you
"要做个令你刮目相看的超音速男子汉"

972
01:12:21,941 --> 01:12:24,068
* Don't stop me now
"此刻别阻止我"

973
01:12:24,151 --> 01:12:26,237
* I'm having such a good time
"我正玩得开心"

974
01:12:26,320 --> 01:12:28,364
* I'm having a ball
"我在舞会狂欢"

975
01:12:28,405 --> 01:12:30,324
* Don't stop me now
"此刻别阻止我"

976
01:12:30,407 --> 01:12:32,535
* If you wanna have a good time
"如果你想开心"

977
01:12:32,576 --> 01:12:34,453
* Just give me a call
"只要来通电话"

978
01:12:34,495 --> 01:12:37,122
* Don't stop me now
cos I'm having a good time
"此刻别阻止我,因为我正玩得开心"

979
01:12:37,164 --> 01:12:39,041
* Don't stop me now
"此刻别阻止我"

980
01:12:39,124 --> 01:12:44,839
* Yes I'm having a good time
I don't wanna stop at all
"是的,我正玩得开心,完全不想停"

981
01:12:44,880 --> 01:12:48,926
- * I'm a rocket ship on my way to Mars...
- Why is Queen still on?
-"我是艘航向火星的火箭船..."
-《皇后》怎还在唱呀?

982
01:12:49,009 --> 01:12:51,512
- We have a situation!
- I know!
-有状况!
-我知道!

983
01:12:52,680 --> 01:12:54,890
- Fuck this. Two seconds.
- Ed!
-去死吧,等我一下
-艾德!

984
01:12:56,600 --> 01:13:01,438
* Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, explode
"哦哦哦...爆炸了"

985
01:13:01,522 --> 01:13:04,608
* I'm burning through the sky, yeah...
"我要燃烧整片天空"

986
01:13:04,650 --> 01:13:06,485
Shaun!
肖恩!

987
01:13:06,527 --> 01:13:08,696
*..call me Mister Fahrenheit...
"...叫我华氏先生..."

988
01:13:08,779 --> 01:13:10,281
No!
不!

989
01:13:12,199 --> 01:13:14,493
Yes! Yes! In the head!
对! 对! 射头!

990
01:13:19,248 --> 01:13:20,791
Shauny!
肖恩!

991
01:13:20,833 --> 01:13:23,002
* Don't stop me
Ooh, ooh, ooh
"别阻止我,哦哦哦"

992
01:13:23,043 --> 01:13:27,006
* Don't stop me, don't stop me
good time, good time
"别阻止我,我阻止我,欢乐时光..."

993
01:13:27,089 --> 01:13:29,008
* Don't stop me... *
"别阻止我..."

994
01:13:36,724 --> 01:13:39,101
Why didn't you just shoot him, man?
你怎不干脆开枪打他?

995
01:13:40,561 --> 01:13:42,771
Ed, for the last time, it's...
艾德,我最后一次...

996
01:13:46,358 --> 01:13:50,613
I fucking knew it!
What did I tell you? Big Al was right.
我就知道!
我怎跟你说的? 大艾尔说的没错

997
01:13:50,654 --> 01:13:52,531
OK.
好吧

998
01:13:56,243 --> 01:13:58,245
But dogs can look up.
不过狗会辨识颜色

999
01:14:00,956 --> 01:14:03,542
- Has anyone fired a gun before?
- Oh, yeah.
-有人之前开过枪吗?
-哦,有的

1000
01:14:04,084 --> 01:14:05,920
- Apart from Ed?
- I'm a pacifist.
-除了艾德之外?
-我是和平主义者

1001
01:14:06,003 --> 01:14:08,798
- Apart from David and Ed?
- What was Ed's experience?
-除了大卫和艾德之外呢?
-艾德的经验是怎样?

1002
01:14:08,839 --> 01:14:12,176
- He shot his sister in the leg.
- I think you should do it.
-他射中他姊的腿
-我想该由你开枪

1003
01:14:12,259 --> 01:14:15,471
- We should all do it.
- How can five people operate one gun?
-应该我们全部都要
-五个人怎样操作一把枪?

1004
01:14:15,554 --> 01:14:18,474
- No one has any experience. We've got...
- 29.
-没有人经验,我们有...
-29发

1005
01:14:18,516 --> 01:14:20,559
- 29 bullets.
- Call them shells.
-29发子弹
-要讲弹药

1006
01:14:20,601 --> 01:14:23,729
29 shells. I need someone
to help me reload,
29发弹药,我需要有人帮我上膛

1007
01:14:23,771 --> 01:14:26,315
everyone else to look out. I will fire.
其他人警戒,我开枪射击

1008
01:14:26,357 --> 01:14:31,403
As Bertrand Russell said the only thing
that will redeem mankind is co-operation.
如同柏崔罗素说过:
“解救人类唯一办法便是互相合作”

1009
01:14:31,445 --> 01:14:33,614
I think we can all appreciate that now.
我想我们现在都会感激他说的那句话

1010
01:14:33,697 --> 01:14:37,326
- Was that on a beer mat?
- Yeah, it was Guinness Extra Cold.
-啤酒垫上的是什么东西?
-是健力士超冰凉啤酒

1011
01:14:37,409 --> 01:14:39,286
- I won't say anything.
- Thanks.
-我没意见
-谢谢

1012
01:14:40,955 --> 01:14:44,083
- They want to come in.
- Get Mum out of the way.
-他们想闯进来
-带妈离开

1013
01:14:44,124 --> 01:14:47,837
David, Dianne, let's go.
Ed, give me some shells.
大卫、黛安,我们走
艾德,给我一些弹药

1014
01:14:50,131 --> 01:14:52,424
- Barbara.
- Oh, hello.
-芭芭拉
-哦,哈

1015
01:14:52,466 --> 01:14:55,553
- Would you like to come with me?
- That'd be lovely.
-要跟我来吗?
-好的

1016
01:14:56,971 --> 01:15:02,268
It's nice to meet you, finally.
Shaun's always talking about you.
很高兴终于见到你
肖恩一直跟我提起你

1017
01:15:02,309 --> 01:15:04,395
- Really?
- Yeah.
-真的?
-没错

1018
01:15:04,478 --> 01:15:06,438
- Ah!
- Barbara?
芭芭拉?

1019
01:15:07,898 --> 01:15:10,442
Are you all right?
你不要紧吧?

1020
01:15:10,484 --> 01:15:12,361
I've got something for you.
我有东西要给你

1021
01:15:13,445 --> 01:15:17,241
Shaun's father gave me this.
Shaun's real father, I mean.
肖恩的父亲给我的
我是指肖恩的亲生父亲

1022
01:15:17,324 --> 01:15:20,870
- I'd like you to have it.
- Barbara, Shaun and I have...
-希望你收下
-芭芭拉,肖恩跟我已经...

1023
01:15:20,911 --> 01:15:23,914
It seems only right.
似乎给你最适合了

1024
01:15:38,262 --> 01:15:40,264
I didn't want to say anything.
我不想说出来

1025
01:15:40,347 --> 01:15:42,516
I thought Shaun would be worried.
我怕肖恩会担心

1026
01:15:44,351 --> 01:15:46,061
Liz!
丽兹!

1027
01:15:46,103 --> 01:15:47,897
Here they come!
他们来了!

1028
01:15:49,273 --> 01:15:51,525
- Stay behind me!
- There's one!
-躲在我后面!
-那里有一个!

1029
01:15:51,609 --> 01:15:54,028
Sorry, we're closed!
抱歉,我们打烊了!

1030
01:15:54,111 --> 01:15:56,405
- The safety!
- That happened to me on stage.
-保险栓!
-我拍戏时也碰过这种情形

1031
01:15:56,447 --> 01:15:58,616
Cock it!
开枪!

1032
01:16:05,789 --> 01:16:07,541
- There!
- Where?
-那边!
-哪边?

1033
01:16:07,625 --> 01:16:09,585
Three o'clock!
三点钟方向!

1034
01:16:14,882 --> 01:16:18,511
- Oh! Over there again. Quarter to twelve.
- What?
-那边又来了,差一刻12点方向
-什么?

1035
01:16:18,594 --> 01:16:20,721
- 11:45!
- Keep it simple!
-11点45分方向!
-讲简单点!

1036
01:16:21,889 --> 01:16:23,724
Top left!
左上方!

1037
01:16:25,893 --> 01:16:28,103
- Reload.
- I'm on it!
-上膛
-我在上了!

1038
01:16:28,145 --> 01:16:30,272
Come on, come on.
快点,快点

1039
01:16:33,734 --> 01:16:35,528
Nice shot.
真是神准

1040
01:16:35,569 --> 01:16:38,239
OK, David, Dianne,
let's block up this window!
好的,大卫、黛安,把窗户堵住!

1041
01:16:38,322 --> 01:16:40,491
Ed, take over a sec.
艾德,接手一下

1042
01:16:40,574 --> 01:16:43,244
- What is it? What's wrong?
- Shaun, I'm so sorry.
-什么事? 怎么了?
-肖恩,我很抱歉

1043
01:16:43,244 --> 01:16:48,082
- Mum, what's wrong?
- I didn't want to be a bother.
-妈,怎么了?
-我不想成为累赘

1044
01:16:51,001 --> 01:16:54,463
- Mum, I don't understand.
- The man in his pyjamas.
-妈,我不懂
-穿睡衣那个男的

1045
01:16:54,547 --> 01:16:57,758
I didn't want to say anything,
I thought you'd be upset.
我不想说什么,我以为你会生气

1046
01:16:57,842 --> 01:17:00,886
No, you should've said.
不,你早该说的

1047
01:17:00,928 --> 01:17:04,098
- Take over a sec.
- What's going on?
-接手一下
-怎么回事?

1048
01:17:04,181 --> 01:17:06,642
- What's up?
- What the hell's going on?
-怎么了?
-到底发生什么事?

1049
01:17:06,684 --> 01:17:09,937
- Barbara's hurt!
- Just take over a minute.
-芭芭拉受伤了!
-接手一下

1050
01:17:10,020 --> 01:17:11,897
Jesus.
老天

1051
01:17:11,939 --> 01:17:14,066
I know first aid.
我懂得急救

1052
01:17:14,108 --> 01:17:17,069
Just hang on. Mum!
撑下去呀,妈!

1053
01:17:17,111 --> 01:17:19,613
- Mum.
- Is she...?
-妈
-她是不是...?

1054
01:17:19,655 --> 01:17:21,991
Just hold on, Mum, you're gonna be fine.
撑住呀,妈,你会好起来的

1055
01:17:22,032 --> 01:17:25,202
- I never thanked you.
- For what?
-我从未谢过你
-谢什么?

1056
01:17:26,537 --> 01:17:30,457
For these. "To a wonderful mum."
这些花! "致了不起的妈"

1057
01:17:32,459 --> 01:17:35,212
It's been a funny sort of day, hasn't it?
在这种日子有点可笑,对吧?

1058
01:17:36,297 --> 01:17:39,175
Oh, no, no! Mum, come on.
哦,不,不! 妈,别这样

1059
01:17:39,216 --> 01:17:41,427
Stop it, stop it, stop it.
别死,别死,别死

1060
01:17:41,510 --> 01:17:43,846
Mum. Please don't go.
妈,求你别死

1061
01:17:55,399 --> 01:17:58,402
- What are you doing?
- We have to deal with her.
-你在做什么呀?
-我们得解决掉她

1062
01:17:58,486 --> 01:18:01,071
- Daffs!
- For Christ's sake!
-大卫!
-看在老天份上!

1063
01:18:01,155 --> 01:18:03,491
- She's gonna come back!
- She's not going anywhere.
-她会复活的!
-不准动她

1064
01:18:03,574 --> 01:18:05,951
- She'll change.
- She's my mum!
-她会变的
-她是我妈呀!

1065
01:18:05,993 --> 01:18:08,746
- She's a zombie.
- Don't say that.
-她是僵尸
-不准那么说

1066
01:18:09,830 --> 01:18:12,166
Move aside. I'm gonna count to three.
闪一旁,我数到三

1067
01:18:12,249 --> 01:18:14,293
One...
一...

1068
01:18:14,335 --> 01:18:15,794
two...
二...

1069
01:18:15,878 --> 01:18:17,087
three!
三!

1070
01:18:17,171 --> 01:18:19,924
- Don't point that gun at my mum!
- Calm down.
-枪别指着我妈!
-冷静

1071
01:18:20,007 --> 01:18:22,510
Don't point that gun at Barbara!
枪别指着芭芭拉!

1072
01:18:22,593 --> 01:18:25,012
- Ed, don't exacerbate things!
- What's that mean?
-艾德,别使事情恶化!
-什么意思?

1073
01:18:25,095 --> 01:18:27,431
- This isn't exactly fair.
- Here.
-这样根本不公平
-拿去

1074
01:18:27,515 --> 01:18:29,350
- Thank you.
- It's OK.
-谢谢
-不客气

1075
01:18:30,601 --> 01:18:33,521
Please, can we just stop
and think about this?
拜大家停下来好好想想

1076
01:18:33,604 --> 01:18:35,439
Tell him to put the gun down!
叫他把枪放下!

1077
01:18:35,523 --> 01:18:37,733
She's gonna change. You know I'm right.
她会变的,你知道我说的对

1078
01:18:37,817 --> 01:18:43,113
And when she does, she'll kill all of us.
That's what your ex can't seem to realise.
