I thought you two might want to tag along.
他们要带我们去安全地方
我想你们两个可能想一块去

1229
01:31:13,614 --> 01:31:15,866
Is it just the two of you?
就剩你们两个吗?

1230
01:31:18,452 --> 01:31:21,330
Well, glad somebody made it.
很高兴还有人活下去

1231
01:31:23,290 --> 01:31:25,334
Come on.
来吧

1232
01:31:38,222 --> 01:31:41,725
'Next, the story of
ten-year-old Enrique Ramirez
接下来报导现年十岁
安立奎拉米雷兹的经历

1233
01:31:41,809 --> 01:31:45,771
'who fought off the reanimated corpses
of his entire family.
独力击败全家人复活的僵尸

1234
01:31:45,813 --> 01:31:49,316
'It's all coming right up on
Zombies From Hell.'
都在即将播映的
《地狱来的僵尸》节目中

1235
01:31:49,400 --> 01:31:54,488
'Six months on and, to many, the events
of Z-Day must seem like a bad dream.
对许多人来说,六个月来的僵尸事件
必定仿佛一场恶梦

1236
01:31:54,572 --> 01:31:58,284
'As we now know, the phenomenon
resulted from the use of...'
我们现在得知,该现象起源于...

1237
01:31:58,325 --> 01:32:03,164
'..not something I ever expected as
a newscaster to have to say on air.
..不像是身为新闻播报员的我
